OL,6,F"Our thoughts remain firmly with Mr
OL,7,FShotton's family and we hope today's
OL,8,Fverdict will, in time, be of some
OL,9,Fcomfort to them."
OL,11,FDetective Chief Inspector Neil Third
OL,12,Fsaid, "Our thoughts are very much with
OL,13,Fthe family of Mr Shotton, who have
OL,14,Fsuffered the unspeakable trauma of not
OL,15,Fonly losing their loved one, but
OL,16,Fliving with the knowledge that his
OL,17,Fbody has been dismembered and attempts
OL,18,Fmade to conceal the remains.
